  "read": "Benchmark-only SASG overlap probe. It uses materialized actual-LI probs/grad_logits and the existing dot-K partial-store producer, then compares PyTorch partial reduction with a detached Triton ScatterAdd/reduce kernel and host-level ping-pong producer/scatter overlap. A positive signal here would justify moving the same contract into a persistent HIP/CK segmented/MFMA accumulator; a negative signal means detaching ScatterAdd as a wrapper-level kernel is not the lever. The selected-row variant mirrors Ascend SASG more literally: Cube345 emits per selected-row partials, then a separate ScatterAdd kernel uses top-k indices to accumulate into compressed grad_kv.",
